parameters:
Konoha-sama, I apologize for asking you to come...
We have an emergency situation.

An emergency situation? What happened? It seems
like the king is not here, but...

The translation assumes that the king's appearance
is deceiving and makes him look younger than his
actual age.
Eh? Is that so...? What is it...?

This is not widely known, but the king's
appearance is actually different. That...

I... I remember a little... Something important...
entrusted to me here...

Just a little more... I feel like I'm about to
remember... Ugh...

I... I remember a little... Something important...
entrusted to me here...

Just a little more... I feel like I'm about to
remember... Ugh...
A curse?! What does that mean!
Yes. I will explain, Maleus, that is...
What is this...? An old... book...

You must not open it... This book is called a
magic book \C[3]grimoire\C[0].

A magic book... Does this have something to do
with the king's curse?

Yes. Several years ago, luckily the king was able
to find this magic book that is said to be
scattered throughout the world. Without knowing
the horror of this book...

This magic book called the grimoire is said to be
written by a transdimensional mage somewhere, and
it has become a single story.

Story... So it's a novel. Is there a problem with
that?
This... is not just a novel...

The contents of this book are just blank pages,
but the person who reads it becomes the
protagonist of the story. It's a terrifying book.

The protagonist of the story...?! What does that
mean??

Within this book, a different dimensional world is
constructed, and those who enter it are forcibly
placed inside. And once inside...

In that world, you first become a child. And until
you finish the story, you cannot break the curse
or return...

Eh?! Does that mean the king got trapped inside
the book?

Yes. Actually, several years ago, the king once
ended up inside the book, not by opening it today.

We were in a panic. And we called upon the court
mage and other renowned sorcerers to use their
magic to bring the king back from inside the book
to this world.

So when he was brought back, the king remained
looking like a child?!

Yes, that's right... However, it seems that the
magic that forcibly brought him back from inside
the book has run out here...

The king was suddenly swallowed up inside the book
a few hours ago...

What the... We have to do something, we need to
rescue him!

If we gather magic power like we did when we
brought him back before, there shouldn't be a
problem for the time being. However, if we do
that, he will eventually be swallowed up by the
book again.

I want you to somehow search the ends of the world
to find a way to break the curse of this
grimoire... even if it means traveling around!
A way to... break... the curse...

Of course, I don't mean to say that Lady Konoha
will be alone. We, including the mages, will
accompany you on your journey.

We already know how to break the curse, didn't I
just say until we finish the story?

If we can just finish the story, then the curse
will be lifted and we'll be able to come back
here... That's what it means, right?

Although it's unclear what exactly finishing the
story entails...

If there is a known method, aiming for that would
be the quickest way.

H-However, there is no way to inform the king who
entered inside the book! The king remains unaware
of everything, what on earth has happened...

I see... Maybe there's a good method after all.
Show me that grimoire for a moment.
Please be careful not to open it...

I will go in and bring back the king, of course, I
will also finish that story.

If the curse is lifted and we can come back from
inside the book, that would be fine, right?

No, but...! That is too reckless...! If Lady
Konoha can't come back, what should I say to Lady
Lisa?!

Don't worry, I know who I am. I am the daughter of
the hero Muramasa. I will definitely bring back
the king.

I also owe a debt to that person... King Leon came
to my aid in that final battle...

Well then, I'll tell Mother that I'll be back soon
and go for a little while.

Ugh... Maleus... It has become even more
outrageous...
Yes... I came here... to save him.

In other words, here... inside the book, that
important person... has been captured...

King... Leon... the king of my country... I came
to... rescue him...
Yes... I came here... to save him.

In other words, here... inside the book, that
important person... has been captured...

King... Leon... the king of my country... I came
to... rescue him...
